.TH MYLOCATION "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mylocation \- Display IP geolocation information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mylocation
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,IP_ADDRESS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mylocation
is a utility script for displaying geographic location information based on IP addresses. It queries geolocation APIs to determine the physical location associated with an IP address.
.PP
When run without arguments, it shows the location of your current public IP address. You can also specify an IP address to look up its location.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-dir " " \fI\,DIRECTORY\/\fR
Set the working directory
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B mylocation
Show location of your current public IP
.TP
.B mylocation 8.8.8.8
Show location of Google's DNS server
.SH FILES
